<div class="commentcontent">
<p>Guava&#x27;s IntMath<a href="/p/guava-libraries/w/edit/IntMath">?</a>.mod does this: </p><pre class="prettyprint">-3 Guava.mod 3  =   0
-2 Guava.mod 3  =   1
-1 Guava.mod 3  =   2
 0 Guava.mod 3  =   0
 1 Guava.mod 3  =   1
 2 Guava.mod 3  =   2    It throws an exception if the modulus is negative.</pre><p>For the record, Java&#x27;s modulus behaves like this with negative numbers: </p><pre class="prettyprint">-3 % 3  =   0
-2 % 3  =   -2
-1 % 3  =   -1
 0 % 3  =   0
 1 % 3  =   1
 2 % 3  =   2
 3 % 3  =   0       The sign of the second argument is ignored.</pre>
</div>
 
 
 </div>
